Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @Potatoes{450%grams} lengthways into 1cm slices, then chop into
1cm wide chips (no need to peel).

Pop the chips onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with oil, season with
@salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, bake on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}.
Turn halfway through.

In the meantime, heat a drizzle of oil in a large #frying pan{} on high heat.

Once hot, add the @Sliced Mushrooms{120%grams} to the pan. Season with
@salt{} and @pepper{}. Fry, stirring occasionally, until browned,
~{5-6%minutes}.

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{2}(peeled and grated) (or use
a #garlic press{}). Grate the @Mature Cheddar Cheese{40%grams}.

Once the mushrooms are browned, lower the heat to medium and stir in the
garlic, then fry for ~{1%minute} more.

Transfer the garlicky mushrooms to a #bowl{} and set aside for later.

Add the @Creme Fraiche{75%grams} and @Vegetable Stock Paste{10%grams} to the
(now empty) pan and pop back on medium heat. Warm through, then remove from
the heat and stir until well combined. Season with a good grind of
@pepper{}.

Pop the @Plain Naans{2} onto a baking tray.

Divide the creamy sauce between them and spread with the back of a #spoon{},
leaving a 1cm border.

Top with the garlicky mushrooms, then sprinkle over the Cheddar.

When the oven is hot, bake the naanizzas on the top shelf until the cheese is
golden and bubbling and the base is golden, ~{6-8%minutes}.

Once your naans have finished cooking, remove them from the oven.

Sprinkle the @Truffle Zest{1%sachet} over each naan.

Share your naanizzas between your plates with the chips alongside.

Add a handful of @Wild Rocket{20%grams} on top of each naanizza and drizzle
over the @Balsamic Glaze{12%ml}.

Add a dollop of @Mayonnaise{2%tbsp} for dipping.

Enjoy!